Prerequisite

1. Install google-gflags (http://code.google.com/p/google-gflags/)

 cd ~/local/src
 svn checkout http://google-gflags.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ google-gflags
 cd google-gflags
 ./configure
 make
 sudo make install
 sudo ldconfig

2. Install google-glog (http://code.google.com/p/google-glog/)
   Please make sure google-glags has been installed before you install
   google-glog as google-glags will be used to control behavior of glog.

 cd ~/local/src
 svn checkout http://google-glog.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ google-glog
 cd google-glog
 ./configure
 make
 sudo make install
 sudo ldconfig

3. Install protobuf (http://code.google.com/p/protobuf/)

 cd ~/local/src
 curl -O http://protobuf.googlecode.com/files/protobuf-2.3.0.tar.bz2
 bzip2 -dc protobuf-2.3.0.tar.bz2 | tar xvf -
 cd protobuf-2.3.0
 ./configure
 make
 make check
 sudo make install
 sudo ldconfig

4. Install re2 (http://code.google.com/p/re2/)

 cd ~/local/src
 # You can install hg by sudo apt-get install mercurial.
 hg clone https://re2.googlecode.com/hg re2
 cd re2
 make
 make test
 sudo make install
 make testinstall
 sudo ldconfig

5. Install googletest (http://code.google.com/p/googletest/)

 curl -O http://googletest.googlecode.com/files/gtest-1.5.0.tar.bz2
 bzip2 -dc gtest-1.5.0.tar.bz2 | tar xvf -
 cd gtest-1.5.0
 make
 sudo make install
 sudo ldconfig
